      "writtenOn": "2020-03-06T18:49:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It would be possible to pass a swarming task through led with multiple different isolateds, but it wouldn\u0027t be supported to attempt to read/manipulate those isolateds via e.g. `led edit-isolated`. We could change this later, of course, but today I\u0027m not aware of any swarming tasks which do this, so I decided to make this an error so the rest of the code could be simpler. Otherwise the isolate editing functionality would need to run for each slice separately when using a raw swarming job.",
      "parentUuid": "c07bd494_37c2aad9",
      "revId": "36d46c4df993a54f6ca93c82d0b107c97450a6fc",
